cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.LG 

This paper involves the use of unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) and mobile edge computing, which are both related to networking and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses deep reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The problem formulation involves decision-making and optimization, which can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also deals with trajectory planning, which is related to robotics and autonomous systems, falling under cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the proposed algorithm involves Q-learning and deep Q-networks, which are machine learning techniques, and can be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
